Then consider the question of methodology.
Even in off-line research, there is no guarantee that the subject is completely honest.
It is not possible to verify on Facebook how much the information on the profile and the posts on the wall are true.
"What you say on Facebook and what you do outside of Facebook, those are two completely different things," Selwyn explains.
