In addition, the total recount of votes in all ballot boxes may be made if there is an indication indicating that the difference between the potential winner of the election and the candidate in second place is less than or equal to one percentage point; whenever an explicit request by a representative of the party and/or coalition that proposed a candidate in second place appears at the beginning of the session.
The total recount of votes may also be made when, after proper addition, it is found that the difference between the likely winner and the candidate in second place is equal to or less than one percentage point and also whenever there is an explicit request from a political party whose candidate has finished second. In this case, the electoral packages for which a partial census has been made will be eliminated.
