President Álvaro Colom announced on Tuesday that he has stepped up steps on the issue of the release of former President Alfonso Portillo, who is to be held accountable in the United States for a conspiracy to launder 70 million U.S. dollars.
This is the end of the trial, which aimed to have Guatemala respond to a request from the northern country that calls for the extradition of Portillo to judge him.
