"We have to base ourselves on the principle that Barcelona's largest park is the beach.
Among other things, its great availability.
Collserola is more complex,” said the architect, for whom the name “gateway to Collserola” carries a “lexicological trap”: we must not imagine them “as entrances to the park, but rather as a demarcation of zones where it is possible to operate”.
The modol, like Roldán and Bayona with experience in the world of urbanism, qualifies the design as an "intellectual challenge" offering "some dangers."
The dangers arising from the "uncertainty posed today by the public place project" after the experience of the 80's, which had "its swan singing" in the Forum area.
The first concern is the very demarcation of the boundaries where it should be built.
"To define something is to take another step," is basically to take a step further.
“It is necessary to bear in mind the new urban and planning tools, because the current ones (with reference to the General Metropolitan Plan (PGM)) can cause a real disaster.”
